<subSubSection id="C838DA176CA1B45EBD5C0725BAE15D12" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="CB58DD3FF9FA02E760884321F6CC33EF" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F507286567D3026D21CE6095F10A0EF6" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
The spicule complement reminds of 
<taxonomicName id="A5FA5297C7EAF044B213AF71A4252158" class="Demospongiae" family="Ancorinidae" genus="Dercitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dercitus (Stoeba) pauper" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="pauper" subGenus="Stoeba">Dercitus (Stoeba) pauper</taxonomicName>
Sollas (1902), but the cladi and rhabds of the triaenes in this species are distinctly thinner (5-27 
<normalizedToken id="9A0DA0F32BF067A223DB0360AF374193" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in extensus, 3-10 
<normalizedToken id="E741CD611A7514A29BD31B52D20DDBB9" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in pauper), precluding synonymy of the two species for the time being, until variation of these features is better established.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="248B0893F0E257B6DDD62B362177C4E3" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
It is likely that the record of 
<taxonomicName id="F5C59B71A4054F7D6714670F2B66417B" authority="de Blainville, 1930" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1930" class="Demospongiae" family="Halichondriidae" genus="Halina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halina plicata" order="Suberitida" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="plicata">Halina plicata</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation id="B952CD61F14242894C8CE675205DB673" author="Thomas, PA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Marine Biological Association of India" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="202 - 209" title="On some deep sea sponges from the Gulf of Mannar, with descriptions of three new species" volume="12" year="1970">Thomas (1970)</bibRefCitation>
belonged to the present species as most descriptive remarks fit except for the upper size of the cladome (
<normalizedToken id="54C5AB02DAC94A9E3A3F2B63D164050E" originalValue="‘chord’">'chord'</normalizedToken>
) of the dichocalthrops which was quoted as 330 
<normalizedToken id="175124076EF4D37C4E7DD06581C90C47" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D668980CE56C125C38B2F6BCB7342B4" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<bibRefCitation id="3F9F73B916341765691F234DEFC7C8BB" author="Vacelet, J" journalOrPublisher="Tethys, Supplement" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="51 - 126" title="Eponges des recifs coralliens de Tulear (Madagascar)." volume="1" year="1971">Vacelet and Vasseur (1971)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species from Madagascar. Live colour was noted as black, which was maintained in alcohol. Dichocalthrops measurements provided were: protocladi 20-40 
<normalizedToken id="9AADC514CB73CBFCAB2D8BC205671DDB" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, deuterocladi 60-80 
<normalizedToken id="99B5F5697068209E3F67658DBA40ADF4" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, rhabds 150-180 
<normalizedToken id="F89BDD99554B63268E050921F3D45AC4" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. Sanidasters were 25-30 
<normalizedToken id="98534DDC4E165E39C3663E4888936610" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. No mention of calthrops. No further spicule data. The colour difference, lack of calthrops, and slight differences in spicule sizes and shapes render it doubtful whether this material belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4FD37DBF6597A5EF6FC46B38A390EB68" class="Demospongiae" family="Ancorinidae" genus="Dercitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dercitus (Stoeba) extensus" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="extensus" subGenus="Stoeba">Dercitus (Stoeba) extensus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
